gomodel:SYNGO_5334  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1j, 2: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for Slitrk1, Bassoon (BSN) and PSD-95 (DLG4) in hippocampal neurons from rat brain cryosections showed localization was \"opposed to the presynaptic marker Bassoon, confirming a postsynaptic localization.\" Localization to dendritic spines was confirmed at higher magnification (Fig. 2).\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Immunofluorescent staining for synaptic proteins in hippocampal sections was performed in 16 μm-thick cryosections from rat brains perfused with 2% paraformaldehyde (PFA) solution.\"\n\nantibody:\ngoat Anti-Slitrk1, R&D Systems, Cat #AF3009; RRID: AB_2190304" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5334" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

